                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Fun, but out of date for biology</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>3</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
                      /
                      <span>4</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1998-06-16</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I hunted for a book exactly like this after reading two titles (Deep Atlantic, Monsters of the Sea) by Richard Ellis. I was looking for something that would, like Ellis, recall me to my sense of wonder. This book can do that to some extent, but it's got a major flaw: a great deal of the information in it is simply out of date. It's especially flawed for marine biology; the supposed senseless ferocity of certain creatures reads like a 1960s children's book you found in the library. I'd recommend this to a person who wants a collection of classic sea yarns and who isn't especially sophisticated as a science reader.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A Must for anyone who loves the sea</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
                      /
                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1998-09-04</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a compendium of short stories, articles and tid-bits with the ocean as their common theme. Anybody who is interested in the sea in either fact or fiction will love this book. I only wish that they would publish it in a hardback edition as it is a book which has become a personal touchstone, not just to me but to anyone else I ever gave it to.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great Book for the Bathroom :)</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
